{"ts": "2026-06-09T00:29:12.664278+00:00", "update": {"tools": {"messages": [{"type": "tool", "data": {"content": [{"type": "text", "text": "successfully downloaded text file (SHA: e222ced09fd6fd4081f7c6dba22dee559d91ed5a)", "id": "lc_5d387791-81e6-4f1e-a5e2-ab2bbc028ab5"}, {"type": "text", "text": "{\n  \"target\": \"127.0.0.1\",\n  \"ports\": []\n}\n", "id": "lc_62c2bfba-b70a-4939-838d-03092fa45dcd"}], "additional_kwargs": {}, "response_metadata": {}, "type": "tool", "name": "get_file_contents", "id": "3f4d31c0-d6bf-4de1-a5dc-1b61239c873c", "tool_call_id": "call_7f59dda185dd43f0b3a120f4", "artifact": null, "status": "success"}}]}}}
{"ts": "2026-06-09T00:29:12.675334+00:00", "update": {"tools": {"messages": [{"type": "tool", "data": {"content": [{"type": "text", "text": "successfully downloaded text file (SHA: cc77ddb26e7675b884cdbb6792774a0807a18afe)", "id": "lc_62a84375-0997-4cd4-b8bf-0793e701bceb"}, {"type": "text", "text": "# Nmap Report Pipeline\n\nA reporting pipeline for normalizing Nmap XML output, classifying observed ports against a local policy, and publishing reviewable reports.\n\n## Project layout\n\n- `policy/` — Allowed-port policy used by the classifier.\n- `sample_data/` — Representative scan fixtures.\n- `reports/` — Generated normalized output and classifications.\n- `docs/` — Pipeline usage and maintenance notes.\n- `scripts/` — Normalization and classification utilities.\n\n## Quick start\n\n```bash\nmake validate\n```\n```bash\npython3 scripts/normalize_nmap_xml.py\n```\n```bash\npython3 scripts/classify_ports.py\n```\n\n## Local scan workflow\n\n1. Keep approved targets in `scan_targets/local_targets.txt`.\n2. Maintain scan options in `scan_profiles/safe_local.yml`.\n3. Store parser fixtures in `sample_data/`.\n4. Generate reports into `reports/`.\n\nThe included scan helper refuses non-local targets by design.\n\n## Maintenance notes\n\nThe repository is intended for local/demo scan artifacts, not unmanaged external hosts.\n\n## Contributing\n\nKeep changes focused, update documentation when behavior changes, and run the validation commands before submitting a pull request.\n", "id": "lc_3a40fbe4-6c2c-4015-a43e-8c48b3ee1c6d"}], "additional_kwargs": {}, "response_metadata": {}, "type": "tool", "name": "get_file_contents", "id": "0dde669f-8239-4c4b-9b26-d372642ad8f4", "tool_call_id": "call_93ba4a0ecc6b434395c015d8", "artifact": null, "status": "success"}}]}}}
{"ts": "2026-06-09T00:29:12.681040+00:00", "update": {"tools": {"messages": [{"type": "tool", "data": {"content": [{"type": "text", "text": "successfully downloaded text file (SHA: a772c8327fd074e7be5234f2fb6c56b495ad0ab6)", "id": "lc_69eb6d67-fcdd-4f54-9c03-c9094efad062"}, {"type": "text", "text": ".PHONY: validate\n\nvalidate:\n\tpython3 scripts/validate_repo.py\n", "id": "lc_e28d3ebe-eaed-4214-b339-b0887ac570a5"}], "additional_kwargs": {}, "response_metadata": {}, "type": "tool", "name": "get_file_contents", "id": "9acfc679-e328-404e-8275-8842ddcd02ac", "tool_call_id": "call_e504f5f3cbf14df4a92e799e", "artifact": null, "status": "success"}}]}}}
{"ts": "2026-06-09T00:29:12.692674+00:00", "update": {"tools": {"messages": [{"type": "tool", "data": {"content": [{"type": "text", "text": "successfully downloaded text file (SHA: ced50c4eda8ebddf735597e6573ee4f9860cd249)", "id": "lc_380f4533-5024-4b84-b4cf-9d252effcfae"}, {"type": "text", "text": "<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<nmaprun scanner=\"nmap\">\n  <host>\n    <status state=\"up\"/>\n    <address addr=\"127.0.0.1\" addrtype=\"ipv4\"/>\n    <ports>\n      <port protocol=\"tcp\" portid=\"8080\">\n        <state state=\"open\"/>\n        <service name=\"http\" product=\"Demo service\"/>\n      </port>\n    </ports>\n  </host>\n</nmaprun>\n", "id": "lc_7afb0ad6-d7f5-4083-ab9f-6c04fc76f11b"}], "additional_kwargs": {}, "response_metadata": {}, "type": "tool", "name": "get_file_contents", "id": "5ed15231-77bf-45b9-b6d6-e783f24b4963", "tool_call_id": "call_b8e9b35eb71c417888064176", "artifact": null, "status": "success"}}]}}}
{"ts": "2026-06-09T00:29:12.703552+00:00", "update": {"tools": {"messages": [{"type": "tool", "data": {"content": [{"type": "text", "text": "successfully downloaded text file (SHA: 4209204908b5c6bac023b5f9842d3dc09fd85f75)", "id": "lc_5e1cc04c-d732-4729-a203-2230e4df0006"}, {"type": "text", "text": "#!/usr/bin/env python3\nfrom pathlib import Path\nimport json\nimport xml.etree.ElementTree as ET\n\nsrc = Path('sample_data/nmap_sample.xml')\nout = Path('reports/normalized_scan.json')\nout.parent.mkdir(exist_ok=True)\nroot = ET.parse(src).getroot()\nports = []\nfor port in root.findall('.//port'):\n    state_el = port.find('state')\n    service_el = port.find('service')\n    ports.append({\n        'protocol': port.attrib.get('protocol'),\n        'port': int(port.attrib.get('portid')),\n        'state': state_el.attrib.get('state') if state_el is not None else 'unknown',\n        'service': service_el.attrib.get('name') if service_el is not None else 'unknown',\n    })\nout.write_text(json.dumps({'target': '127.0.0.1', 'ports': ports}, indent=2) + '\\n')\nprint(out)\n", "id": "lc_04e52c5e-c565-4c69-8b64-7e6d7b3360ba"}], "additional_kwargs": {}, "response_metadata": {}, "type": "tool", "name": "get_file_contents", "id": "ab2a52d7-c358-42fe-8955-fe79cb5595a4", "tool_call_id": "call_7a00a1d11476468ca203b925", "artifact": null, "status": "success"}}]}}}
